00:16:10,740 --> 00:16:11,510
From now on,

290
00:16:12,020 --> 00:16:12,910
there is no

291
00:16:12,940 --> 00:16:14,180
General Lu Lingfeng anymore.

292
00:16:15,180 --> 00:16:15,700
From now on,

293
00:16:16,700 --> 00:16:17,890
you can call me Minister Lu.

294
00:16:18,880 --> 00:16:19,790
It's up to you.

295
00:16:23,030 --> 00:16:23,320
Well...

296
00:16:23,620 --> 00:16:25,180
this is a deal?

297
00:16:26,430 --> 00:16:27,570
You haven't talked about the pay with him, have you?

298
00:16:27,880 --> 00:16:29,350
How much will he pay you a month?

299
00:16:29,660 --> 00:16:31,180
Is it enough to buy me chicken?

300
00:17:10,160 --> 00:17:11,650
Both of you,

301
00:17:12,150 --> 00:17:14,680
are you really going to walk to Nanzhou?

302
00:17:14,859 --> 00:17:16,109
No horse riding.

303
00:17:16,230 --> 00:17:17,390
No car allowed.

304
00:17:17,859 --> 00:17:19,329
How can we go without walking?

305
00:17:19,690 --> 00:17:21,160
But if we go on like this,

306
00:17:21,680 --> 00:17:23,119
our legs will be broken

307
00:17:23,530 --> 00:17:25,530
before we reach Nanzhou.

308
00:17:25,910 --> 00:17:27,460
Why are you so naggy?

309
00:17:27,950 --> 00:17:28,620
You are repeating the same thing

310
00:17:29,030 --> 00:17:29,720
three to four times

311
00:17:29,740 --> 00:17:30,610
every day.

312
00:17:31,290 --> 00:17:32,680
You think I'm naggy?

313
00:17:33,060 --> 00:17:35,100
I haven't eaten chicken for three days!

314
00:17:36,260 --> 00:17:37,610
To be accurate,  it is two and a half days.

315
00:17:37,960 --> 00:17:39,400
There was no chicken at all

316
00:17:39,420 --> 00:17:40,840
at the stage station on the first day.

317
00:17:41,480 --> 00:17:42,120
Yesterday,

318
00:17:42,640 --> 00:17:43,880
the shop was sold out of chicken.

319
00:17:44,060 --> 00:17:45,670
It depends on your luck

320
00:17:46,140 --> 00:17:47,640
whether you get to eat a chicken.

321
00:18:02,890 --> 00:18:03,580
Good punching skill!

322
00:18:07,390 --> 00:18:07,990
Miss,

323
00:18:08,930 --> 00:18:09,810
It's late now,

324
00:18:09,980 --> 00:18:11,240
why are you still awake?

325
00:18:11,730 --> 00:18:12,850
I can't sleep.

326
00:18:13,260 --> 00:18:14,280
Come and talk to me.

327
00:18:14,410 --> 00:18:14,870
Sure.

328
00:18:16,260 --> 00:18:16,860
Miss,

329
00:18:18,360 --> 00:18:19,050
well,

330
00:18:19,500 --> 00:18:21,020
I don't know what to talk about.

331
00:18:22,980 --> 00:18:23,890
Let's talk about you.

332
00:18:24,540 --> 00:18:25,890
I remember when you were nine,

333
00:18:26,210 --> 00:18:27,350
it was me who asked my servant

334
00:18:27,380 --> 00:18:28,370
to buy you back.

335
00:18:28,610 --> 00:18:29,100
Yes, you are right!

336
00:18:29,660 --> 00:18:30,220
Miss,

337
00:18:30,930 --> 00:18:31,980
there were so many people there,

338
00:18:32,220 --> 00:18:33,410
why did you choose me?

339
00:18:33,890 --> 00:18:34,820
I can draw,

340
00:18:35,130 --> 00:18:35,820
you know that, right?

341
00:18:36,120 --> 00:18:36,890
Of course.

342
00:18:37,270 --> 00:18:38,320
Everyone in this building

343
00:18:38,560 --> 00:18:39,480
knows that.

344
00:18:39,830 --> 00:18:40,990
Your drawing skill is so amazing that

345
00:18:41,150 --> 00:18:42,060
all of your paintings

346
00:18:42,420 --> 00:18:43,930
were lifelike.

347
00:18:44,500 --> 00:18:45,620
If you want to learn painting,

348
00:18:45,850 --> 00:18:47,040
you have to learn to read one's face.

349
00:18:47,670 --> 00:18:48,680
When I saw you that day,

350
00:18:48,930 --> 00:18:50,740
I knew you were not an ordinary person.

351
00:18:51,820 --> 00:18:53,260
I've sold myself as a slave,

352
00:18:53,980 --> 00:18:55,660
what's there to be extraordinary about?

353
00:18:56,900 --> 00:18:57,590
But when my mother was still alive, she

354
00:18:57,620 --> 00:18:58,610
once said that

355
00:18:58,890 --> 00:18:59,700
my ancestors

356
00:18:59,730 --> 00:19:00,690
were amazing.

357
00:19:01,040 --> 00:19:02,400
There's even a general among my ancestors.

358
00:19:03,060 --> 00:19:03,700
Xue Huan,

359
00:19:03,940 --> 00:19:05,500
could it be that you are the descendant of Xue Rengui?

360
00:19:05,540 --> 00:19:07,300
Who is X-Xue Renhui?

361
00:19:08,620 --> 00:19:09,660
You donâ€™t even know

362
00:19:09,700 --> 00:19:10,420
your ancestors.

363
00:19:12,780 --> 00:19:13,900
Why do you always sigh

364
00:19:14,100 --> 00:19:15,540
at such a young age?

365
00:19:17,440 --> 00:19:18,000
Xue Huan,

366
00:19:18,630 --> 00:19:19,510
let me ask you.

367
00:19:19,790 --> 00:19:21,480
Do you want to be like your ancestors,

368
00:19:21,820 --> 00:19:23,420
becoming a general

369
00:19:23,450 --> 00:19:24,280
on the battlefield?

370
00:19:25,320 --> 00:19:26,270
Of course I want to.

371
00:19:27,660 --> 00:19:28,290
But,

372
00:19:28,960 --> 00:19:29,910
I'm just a small servant

373
00:19:29,940 --> 00:19:31,100
in your family.

374
00:19:31,810 --> 00:19:32,970
You are a servant, so what?

375
00:19:33,370 --> 00:19:34,940
You'll regain the glory of your ancestors sooner or later.

376
00:19:36,170 --> 00:19:37,490
But,

377
00:19:37,800 --> 00:19:39,470
you must be brave.

378
00:19:39,820 --> 00:19:40,660
Brave?

379
00:19:43,410 --> 00:19:44,430
How can I do to be considered brave?

380
00:19:44,620 --> 00:19:46,090
Anyone who achieved great things

381
00:19:46,290 --> 00:19:47,450
dare to take risks.

382
00:19:48,420 --> 00:19:49,610
For example,

383
00:19:51,580 --> 00:19:52,570
do you dare to run away from

384
00:19:52,620 --> 00:19:53,380
Chang'an with me?

385
00:19:53,640 --> 00:19:54,510
My Lady, you.

386
00:19:54,540 --> 00:19:55,270
Forget it if you don't dare.

387
00:19:55,980 --> 00:19:56,420
You can

388
00:19:56,450 --> 00:19:57,350
tell my father

389
00:19:58,100 --> 00:19:58,820
and ask him for a reward too.

390
00:20:09,060 --> 00:20:10,510
[Yuelai Inn]

391
00:20:13,780 --> 00:20:14,260
Waiter,

392
00:20:17,080 --> 00:20:17,810
Have you seen

393
00:20:18,140 --> 00:20:19,370
the old man with us?

394
00:20:19,420 --> 00:20:20,140
Which old man?

395
00:20:21,240 --> 00:20:22,150
He is looks unkempt

396
00:20:22,760 --> 00:20:23,590
just like a beggar,

397
00:20:24,050 --> 00:20:24,980
with a gourd at his waist.

398
00:20:26,100 --> 00:20:26,660
Ouh, him!

399
00:20:27,300 --> 00:20:28,770
You mean Chicken Fed?

400
00:20:32,410 --> 00:20:33,720
How do you know his name?

401
00:20:34,010 --> 00:20:35,180
Mr. Fed told me.

402
00:20:36,010 --> 00:20:36,700
Mr. Fed?

403
00:20:37,130 --> 00:20:37,530
Yes.

404
00:20:38,160 --> 00:20:39,800
Mr. Fed got up early in the morning.

405
00:20:39,920 --> 00:20:41,530
He asked me to buy him

406
00:20:41,570 --> 00:20:42,570
a horse in the market,

407
00:20:42,820 --> 00:20:44,210
and wanted to leave earlier.

408
00:20:47,060 --> 00:20:47,420
By the way,

409
00:20:47,740 --> 00:20:48,930
he has left a letter.

410
00:20:49,820 --> 00:20:50,690
It's on my cabinet.

411
00:20:51,180 --> 00:20:51,540
Let's go.

412
00:20:53,180 --> 00:20:54,410
Have you found Fed?

413
00:20:55,100 --> 00:20:55,660
He has left.

414
00:20:56,900 --> 00:20:57,700
He even bought a horse.

415
00:20:58,200 --> 00:20:59,910
I didn't know he's that rich.

416
00:21:00,420 --> 00:21:01,450
He's rich.

417
00:21:02,190 --> 00:21:03,550
Touch the money bag with you,

418
00:21:03,580 --> 00:21:04,250
is it still there?

419
00:21:07,220 --> 00:21:08,740
That bastard!

420
00:21:09,230 --> 00:21:10,450
This is a letter from Fed.

421
00:21:11,240 --> 00:21:11,970
What Mr. Fed,

422
00:21:12,840 --> 00:21:13,720
he's just a thief.

423
00:21:17,930 --> 00:21:18,620
Lu Lingfeng,

424
00:21:19,410 --> 00:21:21,170
I'm old.

425
00:21:21,340 --> 00:21:23,000
I really can't stand

426
00:21:23,020 --> 00:21:24,690
the tiring daily walking journey anymore.

427
00:21:25,320 --> 00:21:26,790
I've brought some money with me.

428
00:21:27,230 --> 00:21:28,350
I think it's enough

429
00:21:28,380 --> 00:21:29,420
for months of chicken.

430
00:21:29,940 --> 00:21:32,250
If I've spent all the money and still alive,

431
00:21:32,880 --> 00:21:34,720
I'll come back and ask it from you.

432
00:21:35,400 --> 00:21:36,520
Farewell.

433
00:21:37,090 --> 00:21:37,970
If it's fate,

434
00:21:38,450 --> 00:21:40,010
see you again.

435
00:21:41,800 --> 00:21:43,500
That bastard.

436
00:21:43,920 --> 00:21:44,930
Did he think that leaving this note

437
00:21:45,230 --> 00:21:46,320
will justify his stealing?

438
00:21:47,690 --> 00:21:48,210
That's enough.

439
00:21:48,810 --> 00:21:49,960
Pack your things,

440
00:21:50,780 --> 00:21:51,780
It's time to go.

441
00:22:32,210 --> 00:22:33,070
That's not right.

442
00:22:34,160 --> 00:22:35,320
This stage station

443
00:22:36,140 --> 00:22:38,010
isn't on the posthouse map.

444
00:22:39,540 --> 00:22:40,580
Maybe it's a private station.

445
00:22:41,090 --> 00:22:41,730
It will be raining heavily soon,

446
00:22:42,010 --> 00:22:42,740
it's okay to stay here for now.

447
00:22:50,300 --> 00:22:50,850
Is anyone there?

448
00:22:51,660 --> 00:22:52,180
Open the door!

449
00:23:00,460 --> 00:23:00,930
Who are you?

450
00:23:10,860 --> 00:23:12,890
It's you who knock at my door,

451
00:23:13,020 --> 00:23:14,930
and you ask me who I am?

452
00:23:14,980 --> 00:23:16,890
We are heading south to take office.

453
00:23:17,260 --> 00:23:18,940
It will be raining heavily soon,

454
00:23:18,970 --> 00:23:20,850
we want to stay here for a night.

455
00:23:21,580 --> 00:23:23,420
No one can stay here.

456
00:23:25,380 --> 00:23:25,690
You...

457
00:23:29,620 --> 00:23:31,470
According to the markings on the map,

458
00:23:32,210 --> 00:23:33,430
the next stage station

459
00:23:33,460 --> 00:23:34,600
is ten miles away.

460
00:23:34,930 --> 00:23:36,190
This plaque clearly says

461
00:23:36,220 --> 00:23:37,020
Gantang Post.

462
00:23:37,370 --> 00:23:38,600
It must be an official post.

463
00:23:39,210 --> 00:23:40,290
Judging from his clothes,

464
00:23:40,610 --> 00:23:41,770
he's obviously a corvee working in the post.

465
00:23:42,680 --> 00:23:43,690
Why would he

466
00:23:44,100 --> 00:23:45,140
refuse our request?

467
00:23:50,970 --> 00:23:53,280
I heard what you said.

468
00:23:53,700 --> 00:23:56,260
It used to be an official post,

469
00:23:56,770 --> 00:23:59,130
but it has been abandoned now.

470
00:23:59,220 --> 00:24:02,210
The new stage station is ten miles away,

471
00:24:02,960 --> 00:24:05,590
you may stay over there.

472
00:24:08,790 --> 00:24:10,230
The heavy rain is coming soon.

473
00:24:10,350 --> 00:24:11,080
You don't allow us to stay

474
00:24:11,100 --> 00:24:11,960
instead, you insist on sending us away?

475
00:24:12,100 --> 00:24:13,080
I told you,

476
00:24:13,240 --> 00:24:14,590
this post had been abandoned.

477
00:24:14,900 --> 00:24:15,860
Since this post has been abandoned,

478
00:24:16,260 --> 00:24:17,310
why are you

479
00:24:17,340 --> 00:24:18,420
still staying at here?

480
00:24:21,940 --> 00:24:23,470
Eight years ago,

481
00:24:23,500 --> 00:24:26,300
I came to Gantang Post as a corvee.

482
00:24:26,990 --> 00:24:29,350
This place was abandoned three years ago.

483
00:24:29,380 --> 00:24:31,100
I had nowhere to go,

484
00:24:31,100 --> 00:24:33,300
so I took it as my home,

485
00:24:35,170 --> 00:24:36,650
couldn't I?

486
00:24:37,350 --> 00:24:38,940
Since you were a corvee working in post,

487
00:24:39,340 --> 00:24:40,300
you should let the court officials in

488
00:24:40,690 --> 00:24:42,290
on a rainy night like this.

489
00:24:42,940 --> 00:24:44,020
Whether this post is abandoned or not,

490
00:24:44,340 --> 00:24:45,380
it is owned by the government.

491
00:24:45,960 --> 00:24:47,110
If you keep declining us,

492
00:24:47,540 --> 00:24:48,790
I'll flog you.

493
00:24:55,180 --> 00:24:57,090
Since you insist on staying,

494
00:24:57,380 --> 00:24:58,770
I have to

495
00:24:59,080 --> 00:25:00,710
make things clear first.

496
00:25:01,940 --> 00:25:03,240
This stage station

497
00:25:04,220 --> 00:25:05,630
is haunted.

498
00:25:09,770 --> 00:25:10,390
Stop talking nonsense.

499
00:25:10,600 --> 00:25:11,040
Get out of the way.

500
00:25:42,380 --> 00:25:43,180
What are you waiting for?

501
00:25:43,500 --> 00:25:44,060
Open the door.

502
00:25:47,240 --> 00:25:49,300
Ever since this stage station was abandoned,

503
00:25:49,760 --> 00:25:51,910
I have been living in the wing-room.

504
00:25:52,330 --> 00:25:53,530
The door of the hall

505
00:25:54,290 --> 00:25:57,010
has been locked for years.

506
00:26:19,840 --> 00:26:22,310
I really can't tell

507
00:26:22,430 --> 00:26:25,410
who is the soldier and who is the official.

508
00:26:28,250 --> 00:26:29,350
Since this stage station

509
00:26:29,380 --> 00:26:30,700
has been abandoned,

510
00:26:31,140 --> 00:26:32,780
should we pay

511
00:26:32,820 --> 00:26:34,250
if we want to stay here?

512
00:26:34,810 --> 00:26:36,500
Are these enough?

513
00:26:39,570 --> 00:26:40,720
I see.

514
00:26:41,030 --> 00:26:42,990
You are the master, and he is the servant.

515
00:26:43,830 --> 00:26:45,650
May I know your name?

516
00:26:46,300 --> 00:26:47,970
I'm the new Military Commander of Nanzhou,

517
00:26:48,020 --> 00:26:48,700
Su Wuming.

518
00:26:48,980 --> 00:26:49,780
How about him?

519
00:26:50,650 --> 00:26:52,580
This is my personal staff.

520
00:26:52,610 --> 00:26:53,960
So your official title

521
00:26:53,990 --> 00:26:56,180
is given by yourself,

522
00:26:57,500 --> 00:27:00,280
and you even wanted to flog me.

523
00:27:01,190 --> 00:27:03,050
How dare you?

524
00:27:04,220 --> 00:27:05,990
After all, I've been a corvee working in post

525
00:27:06,020 --> 00:27:07,100
for years.

526
00:27:07,660 --> 00:27:08,980
I know the rules.

527
00:27:09,300 --> 00:27:11,880
Your personal staff who gave himself an official title is right.

528
00:27:13,270 --> 00:27:15,620
This is indeed the government's place.

529
00:27:16,340 --> 00:27:17,380
So I won't

530
00:27:17,850 --> 00:27:18,970
take the money.

531
00:27:19,620 --> 00:27:21,330
I don't want anyone to sue me

532
00:27:21,940 --> 00:27:24,030
and make me guilty.

533
00:27:24,300 --> 00:27:25,700
Since you refused to get paid,

534
00:27:25,900 --> 00:27:26,290
then

535
00:27:26,610 --> 00:27:28,350
at least let us fill our stomach.

536
00:27:29,180 --> 00:27:30,740
Although this stage station is closed,

537
00:27:31,200 --> 00:27:33,550
I still have some food and vegetables.

538
00:27:34,020 --> 00:27:35,610
Please wait a moment.

539
00:27:35,740 --> 00:27:37,280
I'll cook for you now.

540
00:27:37,900 --> 00:27:38,620
Thank you.

541
00:27:40,360 --> 00:27:40,720
By the way,

542
00:27:42,250 --> 00:27:43,880
what happened to your finger?

543
00:27:47,040 --> 00:27:48,890
It got bitten off by a wild dog.

544
00:27:51,990 --> 00:27:53,590
How ridiculous!

545
00:27:56,740 --> 00:27:57,820
In my opinion,

546
00:27:58,100 --> 00:28:00,110
he's right to pick your fault.

547
00:28:00,350 --> 00:28:02,260
I, the Military Commander, haven't even sat down yet,

548
00:28:02,280 --> 00:28:03,710
you have sat there first.

549
00:28:03,740 --> 00:28:04,740
Is this appropriate?

550
00:28:06,130 --> 00:28:07,120
But Liu Shiba

551
00:28:07,150 --> 00:28:08,240
is quite strange.

552
00:28:08,530 --> 00:28:09,610
He doesn't look like

553
00:28:10,260 --> 00:28:11,560
a corvee working in post.

554
00:28:42,640 --> 00:28:43,070
Who?

555
00:28:53,430 --> 00:28:57,230
[Abundance of blessings come at the same time]

556
00:29:16,590 --> 00:29:18,680
I don't know if it suits your taste.

557
00:29:24,750 --> 00:29:25,300
Liu Shiba,

558
00:29:26,650 --> 00:29:28,050
is there anyone else in this stage station

559
00:29:28,480 --> 00:29:29,890
besides you?

560
00:29:32,920 --> 00:29:35,170
I'm the only one living in this stage station.

561
00:29:35,420 --> 00:29:37,540
Who else lives here?

562
00:29:38,240 --> 00:29:38,940
Impossible.

563
00:29:41,000 --> 00:29:42,120
I saw someone

564
00:29:42,690 --> 00:29:44,790
outside just now.

565
00:29:45,300 --> 00:29:47,010
I think you are too hungry.

566
00:29:47,190 --> 00:29:48,270
If you don't eat now,

567
00:29:48,500 --> 00:29:50,060
you may even see ghosts.

568
00:29:51,000 --> 00:29:51,530
Liu Shiba,

569
00:29:52,210 --> 00:29:53,970
don't you want to eat together?

570
00:29:54,430 --> 00:29:55,840
I've eaten.

571
00:29:56,510 --> 00:29:58,460
I'm going to feed the chicken now.

572
00:29:58,780 --> 00:29:59,180
Wait.

573
00:30:03,680 --> 00:30:04,560
Since there's chicken,

574
00:30:05,530 --> 00:30:06,810
why don't you kill one for us to eat?

575
00:30:07,260 --> 00:30:07,980
Chicken,

576
00:30:08,250 --> 00:30:09,820
is for laying eggs.

577
00:30:11,500 --> 00:30:13,020
But I can't see

578
00:30:13,280 --> 00:30:14,880
any egg in this vegetable ball.

579
00:30:15,040 --> 00:30:16,930
What? Are you unhappy with it?

